=Introduction=
[[File:RemodelButtonLocation.png|thumb|Location of Remodel Button<br>In this case, it's greyed out because Kongou has not reached the required Level.]]
'''Remodeling''' is a game mechanic that allows you to upgrade a ship girl to improve her combat effectiveness. Ship girls can gain special abilities and extra equipment slots on remodel. It is generally a good idea to remodel a ship girl when you can.

=Overview=

* A remodeled ship girl will have '''Kai (改)''' suffixed to her name.
** Some ship girls have a second or third remodel with different suffixes. E.g. '''Ni (二)''', '''Zwei''', '''Drei''', '''Due''', '''Mk. II''', and '''Dva'''.
** Some ship girls have additional suffixes to denote a speciality. E.g. '''A (甲)''', '''B (乙)''', '''C (丙)''', or'''D (丁)'''. 
*** "A" can mean several things depending on the ship girl. E.g. Shoukaku and Zuikaku's "A" means "Armoured".
*** "B" means anti-air speciality.
*** Currently only Kongou-class ships (Kongou and Hiei as of January 2021) have a "C" remodel and they are night battle focused.
*** "D" means ASW speciality.
* It restores a ship girl to full HP and supply.
* It sets her [[Morale and Fatigue|morale]] to 40.
* All equipped equipment will be placed in storage.
* All modernization of firepower {{Firepower}}, torpedo {{Torpedo}}, anti-air {{AA}}, and armour {{Armor}} will be reset.
** HP {{HP}}, ASW {{ASW}}, and luck {{Luck}} modernization will be carried over.

=Resource Requirements=

All remodels cost varying amounts of ammunition {{Ammo}} and steel {{Steel}}. Some ship girls require additional Development Materials {{DM}}, Instant Constructions {{IC}}, [[New Model Gun Development Material|Gun Materials]] {{GunMat}}, [[Blueprint]]s {{BP}}, or [[Action Report]]s {{AR}}. Please see individual ship girl pages or refer to the [[Remodel/Reference Tables|remodel reference tables]] for the ammo and steel requirements.

